headline: Big Bank CEOs received serious pay bumps in 2025
summary: CEOS from the biggest banks — JPMorgan Chase (JPM), Bank of America (BAC), Citigroup (C), Wells Fargo (WFC), Morgan Stanley (MS), and Goldman Sachs (GS) — all earned at least $40 million in 2025, their total pay increases rising by $45.3 million. Yahoo Finance Senior Bank Reporter David Hollerith examines these pay increases reported by major bank executives as the Trump administration lifted banking regulations last year. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.

headline: Morgan Stanley upgrades Veeva after 45% plunge from peak to stock’s 10-year low

headline: Morgan Stanley Real Estate Investing Completes Sale of Spring Arbor Senior Living Portfolio for $296 Million
summary: NEW YORK, February 17, 2026--Morgan Stanley Investment Management, through funds managed by Morgan Stanley Real Estate Investing (MSREI), and Foundry Commercial (Foundry) announced today the sale of the final 11 communities in the Spring Arbor Senior Living collection located in Maryland and Virginia to an S&P 500 company focused on senior housing for $296 million.

headline: Morgan Stanley’s AI And India Push Weighs Against Valuation And Dividend Risks
summary: Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS) is rolling out new AI tools inside its wealth management business. The firm is exploring a US$500 million investment fund focused on India. These moves come as a rival launches an AI driven fintech platform that targets traditional wealth offerings.
